The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 19: Unitech has got shareholders approval to raise up to Rs 5,000 crore through issue of securities. The company has already repaid or rescheduled about three-fourth of its existing debt maturing this fiscal. The stock bounced back sharply to close at Rs 31.90 on the Bombay Stock Exchange, a gain of around six per cent from a days low of Rs 25.75.                            
	 Mumbai Jan. 19: Market regulator Sebi has prohibited mutual fund companies from showing indicative portfolio and yields in their debt and fixed income schemes, as the practice is misleading investors.                             
	 New Delhi, Jan. 19: Tata Communications has acquired an additional 30 per cent stake in South Africas Neotel, thereby becoming its controlling shareholder. Tata Communications acquired the stake from Eskom and Transnet for an undisclosed amount.                            
	 Calcutta, Jan. 19: i-mint, which offers multiple partner customer rewards programme, aims to cross the Rs 8,000-crore turnover mark by December 2009, chief marketing officer Neeraj Kapoor said. The company launched its services in Calcutta today.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 19: Bharti Airtel has launched Internet protocol television (IPTV) services under the Airtel digital TV interactive brand. IPTV services provide television content through broadband connection.                                                                                                                           
